  "body": "During the jackson serialization we currently uses (off-heap) pooled ByteBufs using Netty's pooled allocator, but this could be inefficient, because pooled `ByteBuf` still uses `Recycler`s at https://github.com/netty/netty/blob/4ba1c3e7e190bdc9bdd0ece237042f16e843c797/buffer/src/main/java/io/netty/buffer/PooledUnsafeDirectByteBuf.java#L39, which are using https://github.com/netty/netty/blob/4ba1c3e7e190bdc9bdd0ece237042f16e843c797/common/src/main/java/io/netty/util/Recycler.java#L180 which uses `FastThreadLocal`s.\r\n\r\nThis is visibile in this flamergraphs as well:\r\n![Screenshot from 2024-02-28 16-23-58](https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/assets/13125299/96992d53-5e39-498a-97e2-49f584f6ab9e)\r\n\r\nPossible solutions are:\r\n1. fixing Netty \r\n2. bytecode rewrite it on us, again\r\n3. thanks to https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/pull/32858 we could avoid allocating PooledBuffer(s) for virtual thread(s) and just use unpooled heap-based ones (which doesn't use the `Recycler` - in short, what Vertx usually does BTW)",
